					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>A treatise on the laws of inheritance.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="he">Arabic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="42v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Mishpaṭ ha-yerushah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">משפט הירושה</title>
							<note>
								<p>A fragment of a treatise on the laws of inheritance, in the form of a refutation against an opponent.</p>
								<p>The text is written in Arabic, with Hebrew quotations given in Arabic characters.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; an Arabic hand of the 12th to 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>42 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p> 42 folios (+ 4 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 10 leaves each, now incomplete, marked with Arabic words on the left-hand upper corners of the first page (signatures mostly not preserved).</p>
									<p>The first two quires, together with the first leaf of the third quire, are missing. </p>
									<p>Folios 1-9 are the remaining 9 leaves of the third quire; folios 10-29 form two complete quires of 10 leaves each, marked on the left-hand upper corners of folios 10 and 20 respectively.</p>
									<p>Of the 6th quire only the first leaf and the last are preserved (folios 30-31); the same with the 7th quire.</p>
									<p>Folios 34-42 are the remaining leaves of the 8th quire.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Defective at the beginning and at the end. </p>
									<p>Lacunae after folio 30, 32.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>Several leaves more or less damaged.</p>
									<p>Fading ink. Folio 4 and 5 partly illegible.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17 20" writtenLines="17 20">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Diacritic points only partially given.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
